    <section class="topic-hero">
        <h1>SAT Quadratic Equations: The 5-Minute Shortcut</h1>
        <p class="hook">Stop wasting time on the Quadratic Formula when the question doesn't even ask for X.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="topic-section">
        <h2>The Problem</h2>
        <p>You see this on the SAT:</p>
        
        <div class="formula-display">
            3x¬≤ - 18x + 7 = 0
        </div>
        
        <p><strong>Question: What is the SUM of the solutions?</strong></p>
        
        <div class="common-mistake">
            <h3>üö´ The Trap (What 90% of Students Do)</h3>
            <p>Most students immediately reach for the Quadratic Formula:</p>
            <div class="formula-display" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">
                x = (-b ¬± ‚àö(b¬≤ - 4ac)) / 2a
            </div>
            <p>They spend 2 minutes calculating both roots, adding them together, and <em>then</em> realize there was a faster way. Time wasted: <strong>90-120 seconds</strong>.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="shortcut">
            <h3>‚úÖ The Practix Shortcut (3 Seconds)</h3>
            <p>Use <strong>Vieta's Formula</strong> for the sum of roots:</p>
            <div class="formula-display">
                Sum of Roots = -b/a
            </div>
            <p>For the equation <code>3x¬≤ - 18x + 7 = 0</code>:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>b</strong> = -18</li>
                <li><strong>a</strong> = 3</li>
                <li><strong>Sum</strong> = -(-18)/3 = <strong>6</strong></li>
            </ul>
            <p>That's it. You're done. The answer is <strong>6</strong>.</p>
        </div>
        
        <h2>Step-by-Step Guide</h2>
        <div class="steps">
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">1</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Identify a, b, and c</h4>
                    <p>From <code>ax¬≤ + bx + c = 0</code>, note that <strong>a = 3</strong>, <strong>b = -18</strong>, <strong>c = 7</strong>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">2</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Apply Vieta's Formula</h4>
                    <p>Sum of roots = <code>-b/a = -(-18)/3 = 18/3 = 6</code></p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">3</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Done!</h4>
                    <p>You didn't solve for x‚ÇÅ or x‚ÇÇ. You went straight to the answer.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <h2>Bonus: Product of Roots</h2>
        <p>If the question asks for the <strong>PRODUCT</strong> of the roots instead:</p>
        <div class="formula-display">
            Product of Roots = c/a
        </div>
        <p>For our example: <code>7/3</code></p>
    </div>

    <!-- Interactive Widget -->
    <section class="topic-section">
        <div class="interactive-widget">
            <div class="widget-header">
                <h3>Try It Yourself</h3>
                <p>Enter a quadratic equation and get the sum/product instantly.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="widget-input-group">
                <label>Coefficient a (from ax¬≤):</label>
                <input type="number" id="coeff-a" value="3" placeholder="e.g., 3">
            </div>
            
            <div class="widget-input-group">
                <label>Coefficient b (from bx):</label>
                <input type="number" id="coeff-b" value="-18" placeholder="e.g., -18">
            </div>
            
            <div class="widget-input-group">
                <label>Coefficient c (constant):</label>
                <input type="number" id="coeff-c" value="7" placeholder="e.g., 7">
            </div>
            
            <div class="widget-output">
                <div class="result-label">Sum of Roots</div>
                <div class="result-value" id="sum-result">6</div>
                
                <div class="result-label" style="margin-top: 1rem;">Product of Roots</div>
